04:15.255 --> 04:17.464
Excuse me, sir.

04:32.981 --> 04:34.439
My name's Barrett, sir.

04:37.193 --> 04:39.820
Oh, God, of course.

04:39.946 --> 04:41.947
I'm so sorry. I fell asleep.

04:43.408 --> 04:46.034
- We've got an appointment.
- Yes, sir.

04:46.160 --> 04:48.537
- What time?
- Three o'clock, sir.

04:48.663 --> 04:50.914
Well, what time is it now?

04:51.040 --> 04:53.041
Three o'clock, sir.

04:53.167 --> 04:54.334
Oh.

04:57.588 --> 05:00.048
It's too many beers at lunch,
that's what it is.

05:00.174 --> 05:02.634
- Do you drink beer?
- No. No, I don't, sir.

05:08.599 --> 05:10.267
Well, come upstairs.

05:15.690 --> 05:17.316
We can sit down.

05:26.451 --> 05:28.493
I'm just back from Africa.

05:28.619 --> 05:30.454
I'm quite liking it.

05:34.709 --> 05:37.836
- What do you think of the house?
- It's very nice, sir.

05:37.962 --> 05:39.963
Needs a lot done to it, of course.

05:51.351 --> 05:53.685
Damn lucky to get this place, actually.

05:53.811 --> 05:55.645
Little bit of wet rot, but not much.

06:00.985 --> 06:02.402
Sit down.

06:03.321 --> 06:04.738
Thank you, sir.

06:07.617 --> 06:09.034
Sit down.

06:15.583 --> 06:19.503
Well, now, this post...
What's happening is this.

06:19.629 --> 06:23.757
I'll be moving into this house
in about two or three weeks' time.

06:23.883 --> 06:26.718
And I'm all alone at the moment

06:26.844 --> 06:29.638
so I'll be needing
a manservant, you see.

06:29.764 --> 06:31.890
I've seen one or two chaps already.

06:32.016 --> 06:35.352
But they didn't seem
very suitable to me, somehow.

06:38.564 --> 06:39.940
What...?

06:41.859 --> 06:44.986
You've had experience
of this kind of work, have you?

06:45.113 --> 06:47.948
I've been in service
for the last 13 years, sir.

06:48.074 --> 06:50.534
For the last few years I've acted as...

06:50.660 --> 06:54.538
personal manservant
to various members of the peerage.

06:54.664 --> 06:58.250
I was with Viscount Barr
until about five weeks ago.

06:58.376 --> 07:00.335
Oh, Lord Barr?

07:00.461 --> 07:02.129
My father knew him well.

07:02.255 --> 07:05.257
They died within a week of each other,
as a matter of fact.

07:08.678 --> 07:11.138
- So you're free?
- Yes, I am, sir.

07:17.562 --> 07:20.063
- Do you like the work?
- Oh, I do.

07:20.189 --> 07:21.857
I do. I like it very much, sir.

07:21.983 --> 07:23.859
Can you cook?

07:23.985 --> 07:26.653
Well, it's...

07:26.779 --> 07:28.947
If I might put it this way, sir,

07:29.073 --> 07:31.700
cooking is something
I take a great deal of pride in.

07:31.826 --> 07:34.286
Any dish in particular?

07:35.121 --> 07:40.959
Well, my soufflés have always received
a great deal of praise in the past.

07:41.085 --> 07:43.962
Do you know anything
about Indian dishes?

07:44.088 --> 07:47.507
- Oh, well, a little.
- Well, I know a hell of a lot.

07:49.677 --> 07:53.305
- You'd have to do all the cooking.
- That would give me great pleasure.

07:53.431 --> 07:56.808
I could have got a housekeeper
to run the kitchen.

07:56.934 --> 08:01.104
But the thought of some old woman
telling me what to do put me off.

08:01.230 --> 08:03.231
Yes, quite, sir.

08:03.357 --> 08:05.358
Now, apart from the cooking...

08:07.528 --> 08:08.945
I'll need...

08:13.576 --> 08:14.993
well...

08:18.039 --> 08:20.665
everything,
general looking-after, you know.

08:20.791 --> 08:22.584
Yes, I do, sir.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.972
- Brazil?
- Yes, in the jungle.

08:57.119 --> 08:58.119
Waiter.

09:03.960 --> 09:07.754
- We've got to clear the jungle first.
- What, just you?

09:07.880 --> 09:09.798
No, no.

09:09.924 --> 09:13.552
It's a giant development and
they're going to build three cities.

09:13.678 --> 09:16.513
- Are they?
- Mm. Gigantic project.

09:16.639 --> 09:19.432
A matter of clearing
hundreds of miles of jungle.

09:19.559 --> 09:22.686
I'll have another bottle.
And by the way, this one's corked.

09:22.812 --> 09:24.229
I'm very sorry, sir.

09:24.355 --> 09:25.772
- You're corked!
- Listen.

09:25.898 --> 09:29.651
You see,
first we have to build the cities.

09:29.777 --> 09:32.821
Then we've got to find the people
to go and live in the cities.

09:32.947 --> 09:34.739
Where are you going to find them?

09:34.865 --> 09:37.867
From Asia Minor.
There are thousands of peasants.

09:38.744 --> 09:43.248
They're having a rough time of it
and this will mean a new life for them.

09:44.667 --> 09:48.628
Anyway, he wants me
to help arrange the whole thing.

09:48.754 --> 09:50.505
It's going to cost millions.

09:50.631 --> 09:52.257
Millions. Fine.

09:52.383 --> 09:55.176
- I'm having lunch with him next week.
- In the jungle?

09:57.388 --> 09:59.723
Either here or in Paris, actually.

10:07.815 --> 10:09.232
Yes, fine.

10:11.569 --> 10:14.988
Anyway, there's no hurry.
I could do with a rest.

10:15.906 --> 10:18.450
I'm sure you could.

10:18.576 --> 10:20.410
No, seriously, Susan.

10:21.871 --> 10:24.122
What do you think of the idea?

10:26.792 --> 10:27.792
Cosy.

11:02.912 --> 11:04.996
Do you want to go there?

11:05.122 --> 11:06.706
Where?

11:06.832 --> 11:09.042
The jungle.

11:09.168 --> 11:10.835
Mm-mm. Not now.

11:11.671 --> 11:13.713
No, not now.

11:37.405 --> 11:38.697
Bachelor.

11:43.285 --> 11:45.620
Oh, by the way, I forgot to tell you.

11:45.746 --> 11:47.372
I found a manservant.

11:51.252 --> 11:52.669
A what?

11:59.385 --> 12:01.594
What about the landing, sir?

12:05.808 --> 12:06.808
White.

12:12.231 --> 12:15.316
Well, perhaps a little blue
here and there.

12:15.443 --> 12:18.027
But I think the overall colour
should be white.

12:18.154 --> 12:22.240
Well, mandarin red and fuchsia
is a very chic combination this year.

12:22.366 --> 12:24.826
Not overall, surely?

12:24.952 --> 12:27.579
- No, sir, not overall.
- Just a wall.

12:27.705 --> 12:29.622
Yes, just a wall here and there, sir.

12:32.918 --> 12:35.336
You're very knowledgeable
about decoration.

12:35.463 --> 12:38.173
- It makes all the difference in life.
- What does?

12:39.049 --> 12:41.468
Tasteful and pleasant surroundings.

12:42.928 --> 12:45.388
Now you've said a mouthful.

12:45.514 --> 12:47.390
Now, that's your room.

12:52.855 --> 12:54.564
Here's the bathroom.

12:58.402 --> 13:00.403
Wait a minute. What's that?

13:05.618 --> 13:06.951
Box room.

13:08.078 --> 13:11.664
- always do for a maid, sir.
- Oh, we'll have a cleaning woman.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.750
Do you think we'll need a maid?

13:13.876 --> 13:15.543
Well, they can be useful, sir.

13:27.473 --> 13:30.099
Now, look here.
You mind that paintwork.

13:32.311 --> 13:33.645
Oh!

13:40.361 --> 13:42.570
- Is everything all right?
- Yes, thank you.

13:42.696 --> 13:46.908
Tell me of any problems so we can
correct it before it becomes a fault.

14:02.216 --> 14:04.384
Lunch, sir.

14:04.510 --> 14:07.470
- Green salad.
- Oh, that's nice.

14:07.596 --> 14:09.055
No trouble, sir.

14:10.850 --> 14:14.310
- How are they getting on?
- I'm keeping my eye on them.

14:14.436 --> 14:15.854
Are you?

14:20.109 --> 14:22.110
You might bring me a lager.

14:24.321 --> 14:25.864
I'm just about to, sir.

14:27.533 --> 14:29.158
I'm ready for it.

14:30.911 --> 14:32.161
Sir.

14:58.856 --> 15:00.273
How about that, then?

15:00.399 --> 15:02.025
- OK?
- Yes.

15:08.073 --> 15:09.324
Ah.

15:14.413 --> 15:18.750
This is Barrett, Susan.
Barrett, my fiancée, Miss Stewart.

15:18.876 --> 15:21.085
- Hello.
- Evening. Shall I take your coat?

15:21.211 --> 15:23.421
Er, no, I'll keep it on, thanks.

15:23.547 --> 15:24.547
Here.

15:34.433 --> 15:36.559
Do you like it?

15:36.685 --> 15:38.728
Mm.

15:38.854 --> 15:40.480
It's beautiful.

15:41.982 --> 15:44.859
simple and classic
is always best, Miss.

15:44.985 --> 15:46.819
Is this classic?

15:46.946 --> 15:48.988
This isn't classic.
It's prehistoric.

15:49.114 --> 15:51.449
We've always had it
and I like it.

15:51.575 --> 15:54.160
- Barrett, let's have a drink.
- Yes, sir.

15:54.286 --> 15:55.662
Vodka on the rocks.

15:55.788 --> 15:58.247
- And for you the usual, sir?
- Thank you.

16:01.418 --> 16:03.294
Which one do you want?

16:04.838 --> 16:07.048
Oh, this one.

16:07.174 --> 16:08.800
My mother's favourite.

16:14.640 --> 16:15.640
Thank you.

16:24.566 --> 16:28.027
The place needs lightening,
more variety, you know, colour.

16:28.153 --> 16:29.737
Oh, do you think so?

16:29.863 --> 16:33.658
Yes, and tomorrow I'll organise
a spice shelf for the kitchen.

16:40.582 --> 16:42.917
- Would you like to taste the wine?
- Thank you.

16:44.128 --> 16:47.046
- What ducky gloves.
- Barrett's idea.

16:47.172 --> 16:48.798
I like it.

16:48.924 --> 16:51.134
It's Italian, Miss.
They're used in Italy.

16:51.260 --> 16:52.510
Who by?

16:52.636 --> 16:53.636
Excellent.

16:56.640 --> 16:59.475
Just a Beaujolais, sir,
but a good bottler.

17:02.229 --> 17:04.646
- A good what?
- bottler.

18:21.683 --> 18:25.394
- Oh, is this necessary?
- Well, better be safe than sorry, sir.

18:27.397 --> 18:29.899
You're too skinny
to be a nanny, Barrett.

18:31.527 --> 18:33.486
Oh, come on. Don'tsulk.

18:33.612 --> 18:35.029
I didn't mean it.

18:36.740 --> 18:37.907
Oh.

18:41.995 --> 18:43.454
Splendid.

18:46.917 --> 19:00.596
♪ Now while I love you alone

19:02.099 --> 19:05.143
♪ Now while I love you

19:05.269 --> 19:08.146
♪ Can't love without you

19:09.273 --> 19:13.526
♪ Must love without you alone...

19:15.445 --> 19:17.989
Any news from your new frontier?

19:18.115 --> 19:20.533
No. No, there isn't, actually.

19:20.659 --> 19:24.704
Well, he had to go over there
and make various arrangements.

19:24.830 --> 19:26.789
Heads of government and all that.

19:28.125 --> 19:30.960
- Heard from him?
- Yes.

19:31.086 --> 19:34.714
I mean, of course, the whole idea
is in a very preliminary stage.

19:37.509 --> 19:39.594
Still, I'm quite happy at the moment.

19:39.720 --> 19:41.137
Aren't you?

19:42.389 --> 19:43.681
Mm.

19:45.684 --> 19:48.269
I can manage for a good few months.

19:50.105 --> 19:54.692
Oh, Barrett has installed
my new abstract in the garden.

19:54.818 --> 19:56.652
Looks very chic.

19:57.571 --> 19:58.988
Go over and see.

