20:04.620 --> 20:15.504
♪ Now while I love you alone

20:17.216 --> 20:20.092
♪ Now while I love you

20:20.219 --> 20:23.638
♪ Found love without you

20:23.764 --> 20:27.225
♪ Must love without you alone

20:29.561 --> 20:32.104
♪ Give me my death

20:32.231 --> 20:35.107
♪ Close my mouth

20:35.234 --> 20:37.735
♪ Give me my breath

20:37.861 --> 20:41.072
♪ Close my mouth...

20:42.616 --> 20:45.076
You terrible lazy...

20:47.496 --> 20:51.249
♪ Can't love without you

20:52.417 --> 20:55.920
♪ Must love without you

20:57.756 --> 21:08.307
♪ Now while I love you alone

21:10.686 --> 21:13.604
♪ Now while I love you

21:13.730 --> 21:15.564
♪ Can't love without you... ♪

21:15.691 --> 21:17.483
That mouth.

21:17.609 --> 21:19.860
Why don't you come and stay?

21:22.656 --> 21:25.741
For a weekend, a long weekend.

21:27.953 --> 21:29.954
Or a couple of weeks.

21:30.872 --> 21:32.665
Marry me.

21:49.891 --> 21:51.726
I'm so sorry to disturb you, sir.

21:56.148 --> 21:57.481
I'm sorry.

21:59.359 --> 22:01.193
Doesn't he know enough to knock?

22:02.154 --> 22:03.904
He made a mistake.

22:04.031 --> 22:05.031
Mistake?

22:06.616 --> 22:09.493
Well, for God's sake,
restrict him to quarters.

22:17.586 --> 22:21.255
- Couldn't he live out?
- Out? No, he couldn't.

22:25.260 --> 22:29.138
Well, he doesn't have to be here
after he's washed up the dinner things.

22:30.140 --> 22:31.766
Well, he's got to lock up.

22:36.563 --> 22:40.066
- Well, I think I should go, anyway.
- Well, why?

22:40.192 --> 22:43.402
- I'm just going.
- Oh, this is ridiculous.

22:48.825 --> 22:53.287
- Come home and stay with me.
- Oh, look, stay here.

23:02.714 --> 23:06.634
It's a bit late for you, Barrett.
About time you were tucked up in bed.

23:09.763 --> 23:11.180
All right, Barrett.

23:18.480 --> 23:20.898
- I'll drive you back.
- No.

23:22.567 --> 23:24.568
Well, I'll walk along with you, then.

23:26.154 --> 23:27.154
No.

24:07.237 --> 24:09.905
I do apologise for the intrusion, sir.
I had no idea.

24:10.907 --> 24:12.366
Don't do it again.

24:18.540 --> 24:20.499
- I did knock, sir.
- Oh, get to bed.

24:32.596 --> 24:34.221
Have you got an aspirin?

24:35.056 --> 24:36.056
Yes, sir.

24:39.603 --> 24:42.438
I expect you caught a chill
the other day in the rain.

24:45.150 --> 24:47.401
Yes, rain.

24:48.904 --> 24:50.321
The other day.

24:53.658 --> 24:55.075
I'll get the aspirin.

24:56.953 --> 25:00.331
- Would you like a nice hot drink?
- There's no need for that.

25:12.928 --> 25:14.803
- Hello.
- Hello.

25:21.937 --> 25:24.647
- You need some more air.
- Oh, I don't know.

25:24.773 --> 25:26.398
No, you don't.

25:49.839 --> 25:52.508
Oh, God, I'm so sorry.
I completely forgot.

25:52.634 --> 25:55.052
They're beautiful.
Thanks very much.

25:58.473 --> 26:01.767
Every time you open a door
in this house, that man's outside.

26:01.893 --> 26:04.603
- He's a peeping Tom.
- Yes.

26:04.729 --> 26:07.606
He's a vampire too
on his Sundays off!

26:09.109 --> 26:11.860
Why didn't you have them
in your room?

26:11.987 --> 26:15.072
Well, he was saying that they're bad
in a sick room at night.

26:15.198 --> 26:17.616
Come in.

26:24.124 --> 26:26.375
- Your medicine, sir.
- Oh, thank you.

26:26.501 --> 26:28.085
And the post.

26:29.588 --> 26:31.422
What did the doctor say yesterday?

26:31.548 --> 26:33.966
Oh, nothing much, virus.

26:34.092 --> 26:35.843
Put that down.

26:36.803 --> 26:38.554
Oh, put it down, Barrett.

26:43.101 --> 26:44.727
I beg your pardon, sir.

26:48.023 --> 26:50.524
I do wish you'd stop
yapping at Barrett.

26:50.650 --> 26:52.401
It will be a bastard if he leaves.

26:54.321 --> 26:56.614
What the hell would that matter?

26:56.740 --> 26:58.532
What would it matter?

26:58.658 --> 27:00.659
You try and find another like him.

27:02.746 --> 27:05.122
I'm sorry I was rude to your servant.

27:05.248 --> 27:08.834
Look, he may be a servant
but he's still a human being.

27:21.681 --> 27:24.933
I'm afraid
it's not very encouraging, Miss.

27:25.060 --> 27:26.644
The weather forecast.

27:47.540 --> 27:50.042
Oh, there's somebody in already.

27:50.168 --> 27:52.002
Here's the number right here.

27:52.128 --> 27:54.046
Oh, I haven't got any pennies.

27:54.172 --> 27:55.673
'Hello?'

27:57.342 --> 28:00.135
- Bolton 625-45?
- 'Yes.'

28:00.261 --> 28:03.180
Get me Vera.
I'm speaking from London.

28:03.306 --> 28:04.932
'Vee!

28:05.058 --> 28:07.142
'Vera?

28:07.268 --> 28:09.269
'A call for you from London.'

28:11.231 --> 28:12.898
- 'Hello?'
- Vera?

28:13.024 --> 28:14.316
'Yes.'

28:14.442 --> 28:16.443
- Are you ready?
- 'Yeah, I'm ready.'

28:17.278 --> 28:19.071
Hurry up, darling!

28:20.448 --> 28:21.949
All right, then. Tomorrow.

28:22.075 --> 28:24.368
'All right.
I've bought something new.'

28:24.494 --> 28:26.829
- Mm-hm.
- 'I'm wearing it now.

28:26.955 --> 28:28.831
'I'll show you
if you're a good boy.'

28:28.957 --> 28:31.750
- I am.
- Come on.

28:31.876 --> 28:33.544
Get on with it!

28:33.670 --> 28:36.088
- Are you being a good girl?
- 'What?'

28:36.214 --> 28:38.549
Tell her to...

28:40.051 --> 28:42.094
I said, are you being a good girl?

28:42.220 --> 28:44.054
'Yeah, I am.'

28:45.140 --> 28:46.932
I'll be at the station.

28:47.058 --> 28:49.184
- Hurry up!
- You got my last letter?

28:49.310 --> 28:52.771
- 'Oh, yeah. I got that all right.'
- All right, then.

28:52.897 --> 28:55.607
- At the station.
- For heaven's sake!

28:55.734 --> 28:57.192
- Ta-ra.
- 'Bye.'

29:01.030 --> 29:03.157
Oh, here he is.

29:03.283 --> 29:05.451
Get out of the way, you filthy bitch.

29:05.577 --> 29:08.662
- What?
- Ooh, get him!

29:08.788 --> 29:09.830
Come on.

29:16.087 --> 29:18.922
You've mulled
some delicious claret, Barrett.

29:19.758 --> 29:22.885
I say, that's rather good, isn't it?
Clarety Barrett.

29:25.096 --> 29:27.556
In the army they used
to call me Basher Barrett, sir.

29:27.682 --> 29:29.308
Oh, really? Why?

29:31.853 --> 29:33.979
I was a very good driller.

29:34.105 --> 29:35.439
Ah.

29:36.858 --> 29:39.067
I like the changes
you've made to the house.

29:39.194 --> 29:42.613
- You've been enjoying yourself.
- I have, sir. Thank you very much.

29:44.866 --> 29:49.369
Oh, by the way, sir,
I took the liberty of removing those...

29:49.496 --> 29:53.123
chintz frills of Miss Stewart's
off the dressing table.

29:54.667 --> 29:56.293
Not very practical.

29:59.464 --> 30:03.425
Haven't seen very much
of Miss Stewart recently, have we, sir?

30:03.551 --> 30:04.593
No.

30:04.719 --> 30:06.887
My sister's arriving tomorrow,
as agreed.

30:07.013 --> 30:08.013
Yes, fine.

30:08.139 --> 30:09.973
She's happy
about the arrangement.

30:10.099 --> 30:12.017
We might keep her
if she's any good.

30:30.912 --> 30:32.162
Thank you.

30:36.417 --> 30:38.794
- He's a wonderful wit.
- Terribly funny.

30:38.920 --> 30:40.379
- Terribly.
- Cheers.

30:40.505 --> 30:41.713
Cheers.

30:42.841 --> 30:45.551
I'm dying to see him again.
I haven't seen him for ages.

30:45.677 --> 30:48.095
- You won't for some time.
- Oh, why?

30:48.221 --> 30:49.972
He's in prison.

30:54.853 --> 30:56.478
Hello.

30:56.604 --> 30:58.105
Good morning, Miss Stewart.

30:58.231 --> 31:00.065
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning.

31:00.191 --> 31:02.693
- Very nice to see you here again.
- Thank you.

31:02.819 --> 31:05.320
I can recommend the roast duck.

31:06.364 --> 31:08.198
Thank you.

31:08.324 --> 31:10.200
And what are you having?

31:10.910 --> 31:13.245
- Are you better?
- Yes, thanks.

31:23.548 --> 31:26.216
I've brought you a present.

31:26.342 --> 31:29.678
- What for?
- Because I wanted to.

31:37.270 --> 31:39.980
- Where the hell are you going?
- Sorry, your Grace.

31:43.234 --> 31:45.611
You're Irish, aren't you, my child?

31:45.737 --> 31:48.488
- Good morning, Bishop.
- Good morning.

31:55.538 --> 31:56.538
Thank you.

32:15.391 --> 32:18.644
- What did she say to you?
- Nothing.

32:18.770 --> 32:20.771
Yes, she did.
She said something to you.

32:20.897 --> 32:23.774
- She didn't, really.
- She did.

32:23.900 --> 32:25.734
I saw her mouth move.

32:27.111 --> 32:30.405
She whispered something to you.
What was it?

32:30.531 --> 32:34.785
- What did she whisper to you?
- She didn't whisper anything to me.

32:34.911 --> 32:36.995
She didn't whisper anything.

32:37.121 --> 32:39.665
Why don't we go away?

32:39.791 --> 32:41.333
For a few days, hm?

32:41.459 --> 32:43.502
Where?

32:43.628 --> 32:45.045
Anywhere.

32:46.506 --> 32:49.591
Agatha and Willie Mountset
have invited us down, actually.

32:51.219 --> 32:53.679
Well, why don't we go there?

32:53.805 --> 32:56.306
Yes, we could, I suppose.

33:08.444 --> 33:12.698
I hear Father O'Flaherty won't be
at the Cork convocation.

33:12.824 --> 33:14.658
Flaherty

33:14.784 --> 33:18.954
Your man wouldn't miss that trip.
You can bet your last pound on that.

33:19.080 --> 33:21.581
Didn't they have
to carry him out last time?

33:21.708 --> 33:24.334
For God's sake,
who didn't they have to carry out?

33:27.296 --> 33:29.464
I just don't like him.

33:29.590 --> 33:31.216
You don't know him.

33:33.469 --> 33:36.596
- Surely you can take my word...
- I don't trust him.

33:36.723 --> 33:39.933
- Why?
- I don't know.

33:40.059 --> 33:42.769
It's the snow.
It's the snow that I love.

33:45.273 --> 33:48.066
Yes, he looks like a fish
with red lips, I'll admit.

33:48.192 --> 33:51.028
But apart from that,
what's the matter with him?

33:53.114 --> 33:55.198
Stop making him so bloody important.

33:55.324 --> 33:58.702
You've got the whole thing
absurdly out of proportion.

33:59.996 --> 34:01.413
Yes, perhaps.

34:08.212 --> 34:10.630
And where are you creeping off to now,
my son?

34:10.757 --> 34:12.382
Nowhere, your Grace, nowhere.

34:12.507 --> 34:14.926
- Nowhere at all.
- Is that a fact?

34:20.766 --> 34:23.893
Why don't you just tell him to go?

34:24.020 --> 34:25.645
You must be mad.

34:27.065 --> 34:29.524
You just don't care about my...

34:29.650 --> 34:32.652
What it amounts to is
it's my judgment you're criticising.

34:32.779 --> 34:35.864
That's not only ridiculous,
it's bloody hurtful.

34:35.989 --> 34:38.658
- They were gorgeous.
- Were they really?

34:40.703 --> 34:42.496
I'm sorry. I'm a fool.

34:43.790 --> 34:45.248
You are.

34:47.210 --> 34:48.752
Well, I mean...

34:48.878 --> 34:51.963
Divine, darling,
but I simply couldn't get them on.

34:52.090 --> 34:53.130
Pity.

34:54.926 --> 34:57.427
Look... I'm sorry.

34:58.638 --> 34:59.679
No.

35:01.015 --> 35:03.016
Well, I wouldn't...

35:21.702 --> 35:24.538
- I shall be late for my appointment.
- Taxi!

35:28.334 --> 35:30.085
140 Berkeley Square.

36:08.958 --> 36:25.307
Barrett?

36:34.275 --> 36:36.985
- Did you call, sir?
- Yes.

36:37.111 --> 36:39.821
Damned awful lunch.
Where were you?

36:39.947 --> 36:41.781
- Get me a brandy.
- Yes, sir.

36:54.545 --> 36:56.463
That's very handsome, sir.

37:05.681 --> 37:06.723
Oh...

37:09.060 --> 37:12.145
Might I introduce
my sister to you, sir?

37:12.271 --> 37:14.022
She's arrived.

37:14.148 --> 37:16.775
She's very excited
at the prospect of being with us.

37:16.901 --> 37:18.318
Oh, is she?

37:25.284 --> 37:26.534
Vera?

38:22.800 --> 38:26.678
Well, I'm absolutely certain
you'll be fascinated by Brazil.

38:28.472 --> 38:29.639
Oh, yes.

38:29.765 --> 38:33.226
I was in the Argentine, of course.
Briefly, as a girl.

38:33.352 --> 38:36.521
I most certainly found
the Argentine fascinating.

38:36.647 --> 38:38.273
It should be very interesting.

38:39.775 --> 38:42.110
Fascinating, Tony darling.

38:42.236 --> 38:44.654
How many cities
are you going to build?

38:44.780 --> 38:45.780
Three.

38:47.658 --> 38:49.409
Yes, it's quite a big development.

38:50.369 --> 38:52.620
- In the jungle?
- Not exactly in the jungle.

38:52.747 --> 38:54.581
No, sir, on the plains.

38:54.707 --> 38:58.668
Oh, but some of the jungle
will have to be cleared, won't it?

38:58.794 --> 39:01.671
Some of the jungle, yes.
A little bit.

39:01.797 --> 39:04.883
That's where the ponchos are,
of course, on the plains.

39:05.801 --> 39:06.801
Ponchos?

39:08.429 --> 39:10.221
South American cowboys.

39:11.515 --> 39:13.141
Are they called ponchos?

39:15.519 --> 39:17.395
They were in my day.

39:19.940 --> 39:21.775
Aren't they those things they wear?

39:22.568 --> 39:25.153
With a hole in the middle
for the head to go through?

39:26.572 --> 39:28.031
What do you mean?

39:29.367 --> 39:33.078
Well, you know,
hanging down in front and behind.

39:34.455 --> 39:35.455
The cowboy.

39:36.665 --> 39:38.500
They're called cloaks, dear.

39:43.255 --> 39:44.756
Oh.

40:29.593 --> 40:31.886
- Good morning, sir.
- Morning.

40:33.639 --> 40:38.059
- Where's Barrett?
- Um... He's...

40:38.185 --> 40:40.687
- He's gone out shopping, sir.
- Oh.

40:48.320 --> 40:50.864
- Anything else, sir?
- No, thank you.

42:42.059 --> 42:45.228
For God's sake, look at this.
That's not much good.

42:45.354 --> 42:47.689
- I beg your pardon, sir.
- Pull your socks up.

42:47.815 --> 42:49.691
Come on, come on.
Give it a good brush.

42:49.817 --> 42:52.860
- If you'd like to take the jacket off.
- No, damn it. Do it on!

42:52.987 --> 42:56.781
- Would you turn around, sir?
- All right. That will have to do.

42:56.907 --> 43:00.243
We heard this morning that
our mother's ill up in Manchester.

43:00.369 --> 43:03.329
Apparently she's been asking for us.
Might be dangerous.

43:03.455 --> 43:06.749
Would you mind if we took a night off,
came back tomorrow, late?

43:07.876 --> 43:09.460
Both of you?

43:09.587 --> 43:11.462
Well, it is touch and go, sir.

43:11.589 --> 43:15.341
- Well, that's bloody inconvenient.
- I appreciate that, sir.

43:15.467 --> 43:17.468
We could leave
a cold buffet and salad.

43:17.595 --> 43:20.430
I wanted something hot.
Couldn't you make it tomorrow?

43:20.556 --> 43:22.515
Well, I suppose we could, sir.

43:22.641 --> 43:25.893
It will give us time to get organised.
Well, I'm off.

43:26.020 --> 43:28.521
There's one other thing, sir,
before you go.

43:28.647 --> 43:30.565
What is it?
Where's my cologne?

43:30.691 --> 43:32.942
- It's about Vera.
- What about her?

43:33.068 --> 43:36.070
Well, it's her skirts, sir.
They rather worry me.

43:36.196 --> 43:39.115
Her skirts?
What's the matter with them?

43:39.241 --> 43:41.993
Well, might I suggest that
they're a little short, sir?

43:43.329 --> 43:44.912
A little short?

43:46.165 --> 43:47.832
I should say so.

43:49.668 --> 43:53.254
What do you want me to do about it?
She's your sister. Tell her yourself.

43:53.380 --> 43:54.922
Where's my cologne?

43:57.926 --> 43:59.927
Don't come in. I'm naked!

44:01.221 --> 44:03.139
Er, who is it?

44:03.265 --> 44:05.975
- It's me.
- Oh, I am sorry.

44:06.101 --> 44:09.437
- I forgot to lock the door.
- I want my cologne.

44:09.563 --> 44:11.856
- Your what?
- The bottle.

44:11.982 --> 44:14.025
It's all right.
I've got a towel on now.

44:14.151 --> 44:15.818
I just want my cologne.

44:19.073 --> 44:21.532
- What, the one with your initials on?
- Yes.

44:21.659 --> 44:22.742
Oh.

44:25.746 --> 44:28.748
I am sorry, sir,
but I thought everyone was out.

44:37.675 --> 44:40.093
Do you know Vera's in my bathroom?

44:40.219 --> 44:43.513
- I beg your pardon, sir?
- She is having a bath in my bathroom.

44:45.015 --> 44:46.766
Well, I mean to say...
I mean...

44:46.892 --> 44:50.561
Well, after all,
you've got one of your own upstairs.

44:50.688 --> 44:53.022
- I'll have a word with her.
- Yes, sir.

45:07.371 --> 45:10.331
Who told you to take a bath
in his bathroom?

45:12.626 --> 45:15.086
Who said you could use his bathroom?

45:15.921 --> 45:19.549
A gentleman doesn't like a naked girl
bouncing about in his bathroom.

45:19.675 --> 45:21.300
- Didn't you tell me to?
- Quiet.

45:21.427 --> 45:24.846
- Well, didn't you?
- Me? I'd never say a thing like that.

45:25.764 --> 45:27.515
He's still outside.

45:33.188 --> 45:35.648
- Know what I'm going to do?
- What?

45:35.774 --> 45:38.776
Here, take those.
Take one of those and put them on.

45:38.902 --> 45:40.153
- These?
- Yeah.

45:40.279 --> 45:42.280
I'm going to have a bath
in his bathroom.

45:42.406 --> 45:44.824
Oh, you're terrible!

45:44.950 --> 45:47.869
Put on the water.
Go on, draw it.

45:47.995 --> 45:49.036
Ooh.

45:49.163 --> 45:53.040
And I want that...
That all over me. Come on.

45:53.167 --> 45:54.834
Come on.
Splash it all over me.

46:00.257 --> 46:01.674
Ow, ow, ow!

46:04.428 --> 46:06.095
Oh, it's cold.

46:13.145 --> 46:15.980
Hello?

46:16.106 --> 46:18.649
- 'It's me.'
- Oh, yes, Susan.

46:18.776 --> 46:21.569
- 'Darling, I've been worried.'
- Can I ring you back?

46:21.695 --> 46:23.237
'Well, yes, but when?'

46:23.363 --> 46:26.240
- Are you at the office?
- 'Yes, but I'm just going out.

46:26.366 --> 46:28.534
'Are you in tonight?'

46:28.660 --> 46:30.787
Er, yes. Ring me then, would you?

46:30.913 --> 46:32.997
- 'All right. Bye.'
- Bye-bye.

47:09.952 --> 47:13.538
♪ Take me, baby,
to your big brass bed

47:13.664 --> 47:16.833
♪ Eager rocking mama
till my face turns cherry red

47:16.959 --> 47:19.418
♪ I'll say rock me, darling...

47:20.963 --> 47:23.256
Yes, sir? Can I help you?

47:23.382 --> 47:25.466
No, I haven't had anything to eat.

47:26.134 --> 47:30.012
♪ Rock me one time,
one more time

47:30.138 --> 47:32.473
♪ One more time before you go

