♪ Well, rock me, darling

48:23.567 --> 48:26.068
♪ One more time before you go

48:31.825 --> 48:35.703
♪ Yes, rock me, darling,
one more time before you go ♪

49:39.393 --> 49:41.268
Oh.

49:41.395 --> 49:43.688
I wondered who it was.

49:46.358 --> 49:47.984
What are you doing here?

49:49.194 --> 49:53.155
Well, I was just going to bed
and I thought I heard a noise.

49:55.701 --> 49:57.326
But you went to Manchester.

49:57.452 --> 50:00.705
I didn't feel too well at the station,

50:00.831 --> 50:03.457
so he sent me back in a taxi.

50:06.878 --> 50:08.295
He sent you back?

50:09.339 --> 50:11.716
Oh, yes. Yes.

50:17.139 --> 50:18.681
How do you feel now?

50:19.933 --> 50:23.060
Oh, I feel a bit better.

50:34.197 --> 50:36.157
Well, shall I get you
a glass of water?

50:37.576 --> 50:39.243
I'm glad it was you.

50:40.287 --> 50:43.539
I... thought it might
have been him coming back.

50:46.501 --> 50:51.005
- Has he gone?
- Oh, yes. Yes, he went.

51:02.559 --> 51:04.560
Well, I'm glad I'm not alone.

51:06.104 --> 51:09.690
Well, I didn't fancy being alone
by myself in this house.

51:31.296 --> 51:33.297
Can I get you anything, sir?

51:39.763 --> 51:44.558
No.

52:21.763 --> 52:23.806
Ooh, isn't it hot in here?

52:29.354 --> 52:32.106
Oh. Isn't it?

52:34.526 --> 52:36.235
So hot.

52:46.204 --> 52:47.872
Your skirt's too short.

52:49.207 --> 52:50.499
My what?

52:53.587 --> 52:56.005
But that's how all the girls
are wearing them.

52:57.007 --> 52:59.091
Well, that's how they all wear them.

53:01.553 --> 53:04.889
Why? Do you think it's too short?

53:15.233 --> 53:16.650
Are you hot?

53:57.525 --> 54:00.194
Oh, hello, Barrett?
How's your mother?

54:00.320 --> 54:03.239
- On the mend, sir.
- Oh, good. Good.

54:05.450 --> 54:09.119
- Little Vera wasn't very well, then?
- Well, no.

54:09.246 --> 54:13.207
She looked so poorly at the station,
it wasn't right to let her travel.

54:13.333 --> 54:17.294
- She hasn't been an inconvenience?
- Oh, not at all. She hasn't at all.

54:17.420 --> 54:19.838
Has she managed
to do anything for you, sir?

54:20.632 --> 54:22.675
I beg your pardon?

54:22.801 --> 54:24.927
I hope she was able
to see to your meals.

54:25.053 --> 54:27.846
Oh, yes, yes, we...
I had lunch.

54:27.973 --> 54:30.432
I notice she didn't do the washing-up.

54:30.558 --> 54:33.394
Still under the weather, I suppose.

54:33.520 --> 54:35.145
Under the what, sir?

54:36.982 --> 54:38.399
The weather.

54:39.651 --> 54:41.068
Oh, yes.

54:41.820 --> 54:45.406
Oh, Barrett, would you go
to the off-licence for me?

54:45.532 --> 54:48.367
For a quart of beer?
I've got rather a thirst.

54:48.493 --> 54:51.245
- There's plenty of beer, sir.
- Yes, I know that.

54:51.371 --> 54:53.998
But I want some plain brown ale.

54:56.459 --> 54:58.085
Right, sir. Certainly, sir.

55:13.977 --> 55:15.686
- Vera?
- Yes, sir?

55:15.812 --> 55:17.938
- Come down a minute.
- I'm coming.

55:18.064 --> 55:20.107
- Where are you?
- Down here.

55:21.568 --> 55:23.402
He's back.

55:28.908 --> 55:31.327
What are you doing?

55:31.453 --> 55:35.080
- I've got to do the washing-up.
- I've sent him out to the pub.

55:36.791 --> 55:38.917
He'll be back in a minute.

55:39.044 --> 55:41.170
Who cares about him?

55:41.296 --> 55:42.921
Well, he is your brother.

55:46.259 --> 55:48.677
What are you doing?

55:53.516 --> 55:55.434
Oh, you hurt me.

57:08.842 --> 57:10.509
Oh, hello, Barrett.

57:10.635 --> 57:12.761
Just getting a bit of air
in the garden.

57:12.887 --> 57:16.265
- Rather cold, sir.
- Got the beer? Oh, good.

57:16.391 --> 57:18.016
Anything else you want, sir?

57:18.143 --> 57:21.895
No, thanks. I'll be going out soon
but I'll be back before midnight.

57:22.021 --> 57:24.690
There'll be no need
for you to wait up for me, though.

57:24.816 --> 57:27.067
- I'll lock up myself.
- Right, sir.

58:23.374 --> 58:35.594
♪ Now while I love you alone

